<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Auroville Community Dashboard</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --sidebar-bg: #2c3e50;
            --sidebar-text: #ecf0f1;
            --primary-color: #e17055;
            --secondary-color: #b7410e;
        }

        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            display: flex;
        }

        .sidebar {
            width: 250px;
            background-color: var(--sidebar-bg);
            color: var(--sidebar-text);
            padding: 20px;
            height: 100vh;
            overflow-y: auto;
        }

        .sidebar-button {
            display: block;
            width: 100%;
            padding: 15px 20px;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            background-color: #34495e;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 16px;
            text-align: left;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .sidebar-button:hover {
            background-color: var(--primary-color);
        }

        .sidebar-button:active {
            background-color: var(--secondary-color);
        }

        .main-content {
            flex-grow: 1;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f1ece6;
        }

        .hero-section {
            background-image: url('path_to_your_image.jpg');
            background-size: cover;
            color: white;
            padding: 50px;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .learn-more-btn {
            background-color: var(--primary-color);
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        .coding-section {
            margin-top: 30px;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: white;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="sidebar">
        <button class="sidebar-button">Dashboard</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Homepage</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Announcements</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Events</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Forums</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Social</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Directory</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">References</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Help Center</button>
        <button class="sidebar-button">Logout</button>
    </div>
    <div class="main-content">
        <div class="hero-section">
            <h1>Auroville gets a new community platform</h1>
            <p>Auronet needed a revamp. It was taken over and heavily censored in June 2022. Many residents have been asking for an alternative: finally, here it is!</p>
            <button class="learn-more-btn">Learn more</button>
        </div>
        <div class="coding-section">
            <h2>Why Use this new Intranet Platform?</h2>
            <h3>3 SIMPLE REASONS</h3>
            <p>As we build our community platform, we're also embracing the world of coding. Here's why learning to code can be beneficial:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>It enhances problem-solving skills</li>
                <li>It opens up new career opportunities</li>
                <li>It allows for creative expression through technology</li>
            </ul>
            <p>If you're interested in contributing to our platform or learning coding yourself, here are some tips to get started:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Figure out why you want to learn to code</li>
                <li>Choose a coding language to start with (HTML and CSS are great for beginners)</li>
                <li>Take online courses or watch video tutorials</li>
                <li>Practice by completing coding projects</li>
                <li>Join a coding community for support and mentorship</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Remember, coding is more than just writing code â€“ it's about problem-solving and thinking like a computer. With dedication and practice, anyone can learn to code!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        document.querySelectorAll('.sidebar-button').forEach(button => {
            button.addEventListener('click', function() {
                alert(`You clicked on ${this.textContent}`);
                // Here you can add functionality to navigate to different sections
            });
        });

        document.querySelector('.learn-more-btn').addEventListener('click', function() {
            window.location.href = '/learn-more';  // Replace with actual URL
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
